   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER THREE THE CONSUMMATION</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>OF THE BELIEVERS' ENJOYMENT</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>OF THE UNSEARCHABLE RICHES OF CHRIST, AND THE EXPERIENCE</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>OF THE UNLIMITED CHRIST</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>MAKING HIS HOME IN THEIR HEARTS,</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>AS ALL THE FULLNESS OF</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>THE CONSUMMATED TRIUNE GOD Scripture Reading: Eph 3:2-4, 8-11, 16-19; 1:23 OUTLINE The consummation of the believers' enjoyment of the unsearchable riches of Christ Eph 3:2-4, 8-11: God's economy of the mystery: Hidden in Himself throughout the ages v. 9.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>According to His eternal purpose v. 11.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>To announce, to minister, to dispense, the unsearchable riches of Christ what Christ is and has and what He has accomplished and attained: To God's chosen people the believers v. 8.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>For the producing and constituting of the church as the Body of Christ v. 10a.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>To show forth the multifarious wisdom of God v. 10b.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Through the stewardship of the apostles to carry out God's hidden economy concerning the church as the mystery of Christ vv.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>2-4.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>The consummation of the believers' experience of the unlimited Christ making His home in their hearts vv.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>16-19: God the Father's strengthening v. 16: According to the riches of His glory.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>With power.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Through God the Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Into the believers' inner man.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>God the Son's, Christ's, making His home in the believers' hearts through faith v. 17a: That the believers, being rooted and grounded in love v. 17b.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>May be full of strength to apprehend with all the saints what the dimensions the breadth, length, height, and depth are v. 18.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>And to know the knowledge-surpassing love of Christ v. 19a.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>That they may be filled unto, consummate in, all the fullness of God v. 19b: As the Body of Christ, who fills all in all 1:23.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>For the ultimate corporate expression of the consummated Triune God.</S>
   </TEXT>
